    <body>
        <p>Crown scorch and bark char are the two groups of mortality equations used in the Surface/Mortality module. The mortality equation used depends on the selected tree species. Behave automatically selects the equation in the Surface/Mortality module based on the best available science.</p>
        <p>The bark char (also referred to as bole char in other publications) equations are specific to eastern hardwood species and the crown scorch equations apply to all other available species.</p>
        <p>Refer to (<a href="https://www.frames.gov/behave/documentation-tips-history" target="_blank"><a href="https://www.frames.gov/behave/documentation-tips-history" target="_blank">https://www.frames.gov/behave/documentation-tips-history</a></a>) for additional documentation about tree mortality in the Key Documents.</p>
